Instead of submitting a list of a self defined data class which comprises of multiple variables within itself, what we can do is to submit an id (integer) list and then in the onBind section of the adapter class, get the content by using a view model function and then bind the items using the content received from that function. the function can look something like -

    fun getById(id:Int): Flow&lt;TasksData&gt; = tasksDao.getById(id)

where getById is something like -

    @Query(&quot;SELECT * FROM task_data where id = :id&quot;)
    fun getById(id: Int): Flow&lt;TasksData&gt;

then, since it is returning a continuous flow, we can set an observer in the onBind within the adapter such that the ui is updated every time a data change is detected. something like -

    taskViewmodel.getById(getItem(position)).aslivedata.observe{
        holder.bind(it)
    }

